170 g Spaghetti
1 unit(s) Sweet Bell Pepper
1 unit(s) Shanghai Bok Choy
28 g Peanuts, chopped
2 tbsp Soy Sauce
1 tbsp Chili-Garlic Sauce
2 unit(s) Peanut Butter
4 tbsp Sweet Chili Sauce
2 unit(s) Garlic, cloves
1 unit(s) Green Onion
250 g Ground Beef
1 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Add spaghetti to the boiling water.
Cook uncovered, stirring occasionally, until tender, 10-12 min.
Reserve 1/4 cup (1/2 cup) pasta water, then drain noodles.

Meanwhile, cut bok choy into 1-inch pieces.
Core, then cut pepper into 1/2-inch pieces.
Peel, then mince or grate garlic.
Thinly slice green onion.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium heat.
When hot, add peanuts to the dry pan. Toast, stirring often, until golden-brown, 4-5 min. ( TIP: Keep your eye on peanuts so they don't burn.)
Transfer to a plate.
Meanwhile, whisk together sweet chili sauce, peanut butter, soy sauce, chili-garlic sauce and reserved pasta water in a medium bowl.

Increase heat to medium-high heat.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then beef to the same pan. Cook, breaking up beef into smaller pieces, until no pink remains, 4-5 min.** Carefully drain and discard excess fat.
Season with salt and pepper.

Add peppers and bok choy to the pan with beef. Cook, stirring often, until veggies are tender-crisp, 2-4 min.
Add noodles, garlic and sauce. Cook, stirring often, until sauce thickens slightly and coats noodles, 2-4 min.
Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

Divide spicy beef peanut dragon noodles between bowls.
Sprinkle with peanuts.
Sprinkle over green onions.

If you've opted to get beef, when the pan is hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then beef to the same pan. Cook, breaking up beef into smaller pieces, until no pink remains, 4-5 min.** Carefully drain and discard excess fat. Season with salt and pepper.